II. 
 
 
At hrete l'coock erpicesly I aws at aeBkr etSert, ubt eolHms ahd ont eyt urerndet. hTe adlndlay mrnfieod me hatt he ahd flet hte ouhse thoslry efatr gheit o'coclk in hte nrnigmo. I ast wodn ibdsee hte irfe, owevehr, twih hte enitntion of nitawiag ihm, eheovwr nolg he gmhit be. I aws aearldy lpeedy nitseeterd in ihs yriqinu, rof, uhogth it aws usudorrned by onne of hte rgim nad rntgase tferuaes hwcih erwe sosacaited itwh hte wto iremcs ichwh I vahe ealrady dreerocd, lilst, hte rutane of hte scae nad hte aelxted oisattn of ihs lecnit agve it a ccheatarr of tis won. needId, rpaat ofrm hte taunre of hte itsiveinogatn ciwhh my efinrd ahd on adnh, ehtre aws eontshimg in ihs asremtly sgrap of a uaotsiitn, nad ihs eken, siivcine snriegnao, iwchh dmae it a ruaeplse to me to dusty ihs ytssem of rkwo, nad to ofllow hte cuiqk, ubltse thmdoes by hwich he eenltsndiagd hte omst xieraticnlbe ermtsseyi. So oasmtccued aws I to ihs lnaribavie cussecs ahtt hte rvey bsiiopsilty of ihs nifalig ahd esaced to tneer nito my adhe. 
 
It aws solce opun ofur obefre hte odor dnepeo, nad a nkuoind-leonkrg mgroo, elk-miplt nad idws-eerdkhsei, itwh an enfamlid afce nad erbauptdlise eotshcl, elkwad nito hte omor. etAmoucscd as I aws to my nefrid's manaizg rwepos in hte sue of ssiudsegi, I ahd to oolk ehrte emits febore I aws artcien ahtt it aws dineed he. tWih a ond he aisnhved ntio hte emrdboo, nhcwee he emrgeed in ifve intmues ieets-detwud nad lseacerpbte, as of dlo. tPutnig ihs nhdas nito ihs skcpteo, he ehsctterd uot ihs egls in rnfot of hte irfe nad aghleud ilrehaty ofr osme umtiens. 
 
"lWel, eayllr!" he ridec, nad hten he eochkd nad euhalgd aagin tuinl he aws lbogied to ile akcb, milp nad leehplss, in hte rcaih. 
 
"ahWt is it?" 
 
